This paper deals with the study of differential privacy, which is a topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the computation of an optimal bound for composing differentially private algorithms, which involves dynamic programming and optimization techniques (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the complexity of computing the optimal composition, which involves theoretical computer science and complexity theory (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper involves information theory and probability theory, which are relevant to the study of differential privacy (cs.IT). Finally, the paper involves approximation algorithms, which are relevant to machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
